Spacious three bed bungalow situated on c 1.97 acre site with large detached multipurpose workshop, large west facing garden with mature shrubbery border offering privacy and seclusion close to the village of Castletown Geoghegan while also offering easy access to Mullingar, Athlone, Kinnegad and the M6 motorway.
The accommodation consists of an entrance with tiled floor leading to the living room with carpet flooring and electric fire insert with cast iron surround. Fully fitted kitchen with tiled flooring, wood panel ceiling and solid fuel stove with back boiler. Off the kitchen is a utility room with tiled floor, extra storage units and a rear porch. A second family room with solid wood floors and cast-iron open fireplace.
The hallway also gives access to the three bedrooms, two with solid wood, fitted wardrobes and one with laminate floors while the primary comes en-suite. The main family bathroom has tiled flooring complete with a three piece suite.
This is an ideal family home for anyone looking for privacy and space while also giving easy access to local schools and all amenities offered by Castletown Geoghegan and Mullingar.

Mullingar is a busy town in Westmeath. It has a number of supermarkets and chain stores, as well as branches of the major banks. There are also several industrial estates, including the National Science Park. The town recently won a €25m Lidl Warehouse and distribution center which will employ between 100 and 150.

Mullingar lies near the national primary route N4, the main Dublin – Sligo road, 79 km (49 mi) from the capital. The N52 also connects Mullingar to the Galway-Dublin M6 motorway. The town is served by Bus Éireann, and Mullingar station provides commuter services to Dublin and InterCity trains to/from Sligo. The town has several primary schools and secondary schools.
